&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Tees, Esk &amp; Wear Valleys NHS Foundation Trust, a multi-award winning Trust and voted one of the top 10 best places to work in the NHS, is a well managed and financially stable foundation trust with an excellent track record of providing high quality mental health and learning disability services to 2 million people living in County Durham, the Tees Valley, North Yorkshire and York and Selby.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Informal enquiries and arrangements to visit the Trust are welcomed by Dr Venkat Muthukrishnan, Clinical Director for Mental Health Services for Older People in North Yorkshire &amp; York on 07770934351 or Dr Ahmad Khouja, Medical Director on 01325 552304. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please note that all sections of the application form must be fully completed. Should you be shortlisted, you will be required to complete the Trust’s model declaration form A, in line with NHS employment standards.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post may be subject to a recruitment premium.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For any queries regarding your application please contact &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
